He praised the team's performance, and emphasized the lessons cricket and life have taught about the inevitability of both good and bad phases.
title: 'What cricket & life have taught us...': Samson praises team's character

description: The letter, penned by Siddaramaiah to PM Modi, highlights the severity of the accusations leveled against Prajwal Revanna, emphasizing the shock and concern felt not only in Karnataka but across the nation. It underscores the disgraceful act of Prajwal Revanna fleeing the country to Germany on April 27, 2024, using his diplomatic passport, shortly after the news of his alleged heinous actions surfaced and just hours before the filing of the first FIR against him.
title: Siddaramaiah writes to PM to cancel Prajwal's diplomatic passport

description: 5 people died and 35 were injured in Iowa due to tornadoes, causing destruction in Greenfield. The Greenfield tornado ripped through the community of 2,000, roughly 55 miles (88.5 kilometers) southwest of Des Moines, destroying homes, splintering trees, and crumpling cars. The tornado also ripped apart and collapsed enormous power-generating wind turbines many kilometers outside of the city.
title: At least 5 dead, 35 injured as multiple tornadoes hit Iowa

description: A nursing officer at AIIMS Rishikesh was detained by the police after a junior resident doctor accused him of molesting her in the trauma surgery unit. The accused was suspended and an internal inquiry is ongoing following the doctor's complaint. The incident led to protests by medical students demanding action against the nursing officer.
title: Police vehicle enters Aiims to arrest sexual abuse accused

description: The Reserve Bank of India added 24 tonnes of gold to its reserves between January and April this year to diversify reserves during volatility amid geopolitical tensions. Central banks, including emerging markets, are increasing gold reserves due to its store of value and rising prices in response to global uncertainty.
title: Why RBI is stocking up aggressively on gold reserves

description: The Juvenile Justice Board in Pune granted bail to a 17-year-old driver who allegedly killed two techies from MP. The board will monitor the teenager at an observation home and conduct psychological tests and counselling under Section 15 of the Juvenile Justice Act.
title: Pune Porsche crash: Panel to carry out psychological tests on teen

description: Mitchell McClenaghan, a former Mumbai Indians pacer, has questioned the legitimacy of a 'crucial' run-out during the Indian Premier League 2024 Eliminator between Rajasthan Royals and Royal Challengers Bengaluru. Despite the run-out, which involved Virat Kohli and Cameron Green, RCB lost by four wickets and dropped out of the tournament.
title: 'Rules changed?': Ex-MI star questions 'run-out' decision

description: Taiwan's military mobilized its forces and said it was confident it could protect the island, after China started two days of "punishment" drills around Taiwan on Thursday in what it said was a response to "separatist acts". The exercises, in the Taiwan Strait and around groups of Taiwan-controlled islands that sit next to the Chinese coast, come just three days after Lai Ching-te took office as Taiwan's new president, a man Beijing detests as a "separatist".
title: China conducts biggest ‘blockade’ drills around Taiwan

description: Bangladesh MP Anwarul Azim Anar, 56, was murdered in Kolkata. His body has not been found yet, with three arrests made in Bangladesh related to the case.
title: Bangladesh MP murder mystery deepens: 'Body not found'

description: An explosion has occurred at an apartment building in Harbin, a city in northeastern China, state media reported. Casualties are unknown. Xinhua news agency said the explosion occurred at roughly 7 a.m. Thursday. Rescuers were on scene.
title: Explosion at apartment building in China's Harbin: Reports

description: A child in Australia is the first human case of the H5N1 virus, believed to be contracted in India. Health officials confirm the rare avian influenza case, emphasizing the potential risks and symptoms. Australia faces its first H5N1 case amidst global outbreaks in birds.
title: Australia's 1st human case of bird flu confirmed; got infection in India

description: Glenn Maxwell, known as the 'Big Show', was dismissed for a golden duck in the IPL 2024 Eliminator match against Rajasthan Royals. Ravichandran Ashwin's critical over, including removing Cameron Green, led to Maxwell's duck, resulting in RCB's downfall and tournament exit. description: Buddha Purnima 2024, also popularly known as Buddha Jayanti or Vesak, is an immensely important festival celebrated by Buddhist followers all around the world. This special day honours the birth of Gautam Buddha, the founder of Buddhism. On this auspicious occasion, Buddhists remember the life and teachings of Buddha, emphasizing great values of compassion, non-violence, and spiritual peace and enlightenment.
title: Happy Buddha Purnima: Quotes, wishes, images to share
